                            <comment id="13989060" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 4 May 2014 17:38:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It was a bad idea not to use the build-in mapping of a type1c font as special character can&apos;t be extracted anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I reimplemented the feature in revision 1592393. I&apos;m going to backport the changes to the branch as well, but I&apos;ve to run some tests first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989736" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 17:25:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My last changes to the trunk introduced a regression with the extraction of the file attach to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1770&quot; title=&quot;ExtractText gets all &amp;quot;?&amp;quot; when pdf &amp;#39;s font is instance of PDType1Font&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1770&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1770&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I&apos;ve fixed that in revision 1592577.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I already ported my first changes to the branch and committed them in revision 1592566. But I&apos;ve to admit that those changes are not working for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1770&quot; title=&quot;ExtractText gets all &amp;quot;?&amp;quot; when pdf &amp;#39;s font is instance of PDType1Font&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1770&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1770&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I&apos;m still investigating.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989763" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 17:49:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added the changes from 1592577 to the branch too and fixed the regression I&apos;d introduced in revision 1592566. I&apos;ve done both in revision 1592586&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989772" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 17:57:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess we are done here. &lt;br/&gt;
BTW: in the case of the referenced pdf we are better than acrobat reader, which can&apos;t extract those special characters &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989947" author="tilman" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 20:43:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t build 1.8, TestTextStripper fails. The deeper cause is PDType1CFont&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;character = Encoding.getCharacterForName(name);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which doesn&apos;t exist in that class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989962" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 20:56:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, the test works fine for me. Did you update to the latest version? What exactly doesn&apos;t work?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989970" author="tilman" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 21:01:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t compile when doing &quot;clean and build&quot;, because the &quot;Encoding&quot; class  doesn&apos;t have a getCharacterForName() method. That method appeared today for the first time in the PDType1CFont class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989972" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 21:02:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Forget my former comment, I simply forgot to commit my changes in Encoding. I&apos;ve caught up those missing changes in revision 1592629&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the inconvience!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989988" author="tilman" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 21:20:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, it works now &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
